qas.question: What were some impoverished szlachta forced to do?

answers.text: to become tenants of the wealthier gentry.

qas.question: Did the tenants of the wealthier genrty lose their nobility?
What was one noble thing the poor szlachta did?

context: As some szlachta were poorer than some non-noble gentry, some particularly impoverished szlachta were forced <a1_0>to become tenants of the wealthier gentry.<a1_0/> In doing so, however, these szlachta <a3_0>retained all their constitutional prerogatives<a3_0/>, as it was not wealth or lifestyle (obtainable by the gentry), but <a0_0>hereditary juridical status<a0_0/>, that determined <a2_0>no<a2_0/>bility.
